message: The optimal strategy is to process three out of four creatures, then combine them. Small creatures (e.g., bee, frog, butterfly, trout, pufferfish) gain max value (25) from the full 'mutant>growth>mutant>growth' (MGMG) sequence. Medium creatures (e.g., zebra, monkey, crab, kangaroo, squid) gain max value (30) from the full MGMG sequence. Large creatures (e.g., shark, lion, panda, elephant, giraffe) *lose* value if you apply the final 'growth' step; they are best processed with 'mutant>growth>mutant' (MGM) to reach value 30. Combine the three highest-value processed items (e.g., two small and one medium, or two medium and one large processed with MGM) to reach scores in the 85-95 range. Do not attempt to process or combine all four, as this leads to lower scores or errors.

message: The most effective strategy is a three-step tool sequence: apply 'mutation catalyst' then 'growth serum' then 'mutation catalyst' to each initial ingredient. This transforms them into 'grown super-mutant' items, typically valued between 20-30. Once you have several, combine up to three of these 'grown super-mutant' items. message: The most effective strategy is to use the tool sequence 'mutation catalyst > growth serum > mutation catalyst' on individual creatures. This creates a 'grown super-mutant' item with a value of 20-30. Crucially, *do not* apply the 'growth serum' a second time to create a 'super-grown' item, as this often drops the value to 0. After creating several 'grown super-mutant' items (up to 3), combine them. Combining three such items can yield values around 65. Avoid applying tools to items that are already combined, as this often results in negative values. If tools are limited, combining a 'lives in water' creature with a 'lives in air' creature typically yields a value of 5.

message: The 'mutant>growth>mutant>growth' sequence works well for small and medium creatures to get them to high individual values (around 25-30). For large creatures, stop after the second 'mutation catalyst' (mutant>growth>mutant) as the final 'growth serum' often drops their value to 0. After preparing 3 creatures this way, combine them. Mixing creatures from different environments (e.g., land and water) often results in very high combined values. Don't try to combine all four; 3 is usually optimal.
